00:14:55.983 --> 00:14:59.774
- Why didn't you tell us anything?
- What would it change? Calm down!

233
00:14:59.774 --> 00:15:02.774
- Damn. so you can talk
in normal language!

234
00:15:02.774 --> 00:15:05.816
- Yes. thank you! So what's the difference? Huh?

235
00:15:07.941 --> 00:15:09.149
Well?

236
00:15:09.816 --> 00:15:13.316
- No. don't think about it. normally
it wouldn't be a problem.

237
00:15:13.650 --> 00:15:14.691
- That's not the point.

238
00:15:14.816 --> 00:15:17.691
- Besides. we already kissed once.
- Stop it. what are you talking about?

239
00:15:17.691 --> 00:15:18.733
- What?

240
00:15:18.733 --> 00:15:23.066
- It's true. I remember too. At the party at home
of Carine Mercier.

241
00:15:24.483 --> 00:15:26.650
- Frank. you're a peeping Tom!

242
00:15:26.650 --> 00:15:29.066
- Then I took three pills
of ecstasy. and I was impressed.

243
00:15:29.066 --> 00:15:31.441
- Okay. I get it! I'll do it.
if you're so impatient!

244
00:15:50.149 --> 00:15:51.275
- Ma che cavolo?

245
00:16:20.233 --> 00:16:21.441
- Matt?

246
00:16:56.108 --> 00:16:57.608
- When you're dumb.

247
00:17:53.191 --> 00:17:56.691
- Oh. that's nice.
I could fucking die right now!

248
00:18:00.024 --> 00:18:03.525
- Do I have to wear this?
- Yes. you do. It's necessary for contrast.

249
00:18:06.774 --> 00:18:09.608
- And this Vegeta
will she stay here?

250
00:18:10.525 --> 00:18:14.483
- What vegeta?
- Your stupid Dragonball.

251
00:18:14.525 --> 00:18:15.941
- Is that the HBO show?

252
00:18:15.941 --> 00:18:19.691
- Okay. forget it. He can't stay there.

253
00:18:20.525 --> 00:18:23.566
You can finish minding your own business
upstairs?

254
00:18:23.566 --> 00:18:25.983
- Well. your creation.

255
00:18:33.566 --> 00:18:36.108
- Oh. Mine. Oh. God. All right.

256
00:18:36.108 --> 00:18:38.733
What you need to know. This movie...

257
00:18:38.733 --> 00:18:44.983
is super impressionist but. at the same time.
expressionist.

258
00:18:45.024 --> 00:18:46.399
You understand. don't you?

259
00:18:51.275 --> 00:18:56.858
- I'm certainly not an expert. but in my opinion.
impressionism and expressionism

260
00:18:56.858 --> 00:19:01.024
are mutually exclusive.
Aren't they?

261
00:19:01.066 --> 00:19:04.149
- Okay. then I'll explain
the plot of the movie.

262
00:19:04.191 --> 00:19:07.941
Then there are two women...
or two men. it doesn't matter

263
00:19:07.941 --> 00:19:10.399
who are sitting next to each other and all of a sudden - bang!

264
00:19:10.441 --> 00:19:13.483
Kiss. That is
such a natural thing.

265
00:19:14.774 --> 00:19:17.316
- I know you care and all. of course.

266
00:19:17.358 --> 00:19:22.608
I don't want to dampen your spirits.
but we're still two guys.

267
00:19:23.149 --> 00:19:24.691
- Lord. what a little gem you are.

268
00:19:25.483 --> 00:19:28.149
Okay. it's a small ambush. because

269
00:19:29.066 --> 00:19:32.441
your generation has visions
so backward.

270
00:19:32.483 --> 00:19:37.483
But I personally. for example. feel
not to stick me on a label.

271
00:19:37.483 --> 00:19:39.733
From the outside - yes. there is a difference.

272
00:19:39.774 --> 00:19:44.650
but if you don't consider the beard and all
this male bullshit. how can you tell?

273
00:19:45.358 --> 00:19:47.566
- Really? They kissed in high school?

274
00:19:47.608 --> 00:19:48.900
- Classic. huh?

275
00:19:48.941 --> 00:19:50.941
- I don't know. it seems like Matt's already forgotten everything.

276
00:19:51.525 --> 00:19:54.149
And I studied in parallel with him myself.
but and this is the first I've heard of this.

277
00:19:59.108 --> 00:20:00.191
- What?

278
00:20:00.900 --> 00:20:04.358
- You never said the stupidest thing in your life.
- What?

279
00:20:04.900 --> 00:20:06.316
- And you study psychology at Cambridge!

280
00:20:06.316 --> 00:20:08.191
- You think Matt would have gotten a tattoo:

281
00:20:08.191 --> 00:20:10.733
"I made out with Max in high school.
Never forgot!"

282
00:20:11.941 --> 00:20:13.275
- Idiots.

283
00:20:13.275 --> 00:20:16.233
- Sir. this is the most
beautiful in my life. Thank you!

284
00:20:16.233 --> 00:20:18.024
- Frank. you're like that janitor in college.

285
00:20:18.066 --> 00:20:20.566
that solves unsolvable at night
math problems.

286
00:20:20.608 --> 00:20:24.316
- And that he found the binomial theorem. Let's go!

287
00:20:24.358 --> 00:20:28.149
- Our Frank - Good Will Hunting. That
studied all the books in the library.

288
00:20:28.191 --> 00:20:30.608
- I might be crazy.
but my brain is fine.

289
00:20:30.650 --> 00:20:33.608
- Okay. genius. a little modesty.
- Come on.

290
00:20:36.483 --> 00:20:38.650
- Get out of my eyes. you freaks!

291
00:20:42.024 --> 00:20:43.316
- All right. let's go.

292
00:20:43.941 --> 00:20:45.191
Ready?

293
00:20:45.733 --> 00:20:50.733
Then
four. three. two. one. Action.

294
00:21:52.733 --> 00:21:56.149
- Max? Max. are you asleep?

295
00:24:30.858 --> 00:24:35.691
- Do you need anything?
- I'm looking for Rivette.

296
00:24:36.399 --> 00:24:38.399
- Rivets?
- Yeah.

297
00:24:38.566 --> 00:24:43.608
- You're lost. young man!
Want me to give you a ride in my car?

298
00:24:58.275 --> 00:25:00.358
- Are you crazy to swim so far away?

299
00:25:32.858 --> 00:25:35.066
- Damn it. I'm lost.

300
00:25:35.733 --> 00:25:37.191
- Why did you go in the first place?

301
00:25:44.024 --> 00:25:45.191
- You all right. Matt?

302
00:25:58.358 --> 00:26:01.525
Twelve days
before we leave for Australia.

303
00:28:02.108 --> 00:28:04.191
- Your father can be proud of you.

304
00:28:04.233 --> 00:28:07.774
I even took the liberty of writing
a text message to Mr. Ruiz

305
00:28:07.816 --> 00:28:11.399
to inform him of his son's achievements.

306
00:28:12.316 --> 00:28:15.441
Of course. I shouldn't like running
too much but

307
00:28:15.941 --> 00:28:19.358
your work is very impressive.

308
00:28:20.275 --> 00:28:25.358
I don't think we need to give an exact date in the near future...

309
00:28:25.399 --> 00:28:29.650
let's just say - in the near future.

310
00:28:30.650 --> 00:28:33.608
So. I'm thinking

311
00:28:33.608 --> 00:28:37.399
empower you
within the company.

312
00:28:37.858 --> 00:28:40.608
And as I like to say: a chair
with a view of Montreal!

313
00:28:48.900 --> 00:28:50.483
Well. what do you say?

314
00:28:53.108 --> 00:28:57.066
- No. I understand. I. of course...

315
00:28:58.275 --> 00:29:01.483
Of course I'm very happy to hear that.

316
00:29:02.441 --> 00:29:05.525
- You know. Matt.
- No. no. Gilles. I get it.

317
00:29:05.525 --> 00:29:06.983
- Say no more!

318
00:29:08.941 --> 00:29:13.941
At your age it's enough
natural to doubt yourself.

319
00:29:13.941 --> 00:29:18.108
You experiment.
you try new things.

320
00:29:19.983 --> 00:29:22.650
One day you wake up and - oops!

321
00:29:23.399 --> 00:29:25.650
You realize you're stuck in a swamp.

322
00:29:27.233 --> 00:29:32.024
Yes. in my life I'm used to seeing
people engaged in the same things over and over again

323
00:29:32.483 --> 00:29:35.275
who find out they have
I need something else entirely.

324
00:29:39.275 --> 00:29:42.733
So let's forget about the promotion

325
00:29:42.733 --> 00:29:45.441
for a while and get back to the Thompson case.

326
00:29:46.191 --> 00:29:49.316
Where is he? Ah. here. This morning
I talked to the lady...

327
00:29:49.316 --> 00:29:54.066
What was her name? God. I always get confused
names. Ma'am. ma'am. ma'am...

328
00:29:57.191 --> 00:29:58.399
Ma'am.

329
00:30:04.191 --> 00:30:08.316
Just a moment. where did I put it?
Ah. here.

330
00:30:16.108 --> 00:30:17.358
- What are you doing?

331
00:30:19.066 --> 00:30:21.983
- I cook pasta.  Just the way you like it.

332
00:30:27.149 --> 00:30:28.608
- Your brother hasn't been in touch?

333
00:30:33.024 --> 00:30:36.233
- You still like pasta?
You liked it last time.

334
00:30:36.233 --> 00:30:37.358
- Yeah.

335
00:30:39.983 --> 00:30:42.275
- This little fucker
he's not answering his phone.

336
00:30:44.983 --> 00:30:46.441
I don't know why.

337
00:30:57.941 --> 00:31:00.024
- No need to stick to the cigarette.
you barely open your eyes.

338
00:31:12.566 --> 00:31:14.108
Well. yeah.

339
00:31:19.816 --> 00:31:21.191
- What are you doing?

340
00:31:31.691 --> 00:31:32.858
Well.

341
00:31:38.108 --> 00:31:40.024
- Stop playing games. Give it to me.

342
00:32:05.941 --> 00:32:09.608
- I'm seeing Aunt Jeanette tomorrow.
- That's lucky.

343
00:32:12.816 --> 00:32:14.525
- He's almost retired.

344
00:32:14.566 --> 00:32:16.275
He can take care of you
while I'm gone.

345
00:32:16.608 --> 00:32:20.816
- I don't want to see her hysterical.
I'm not an invalid!

346
00:32:21.816 --> 00:32:24.233
- Someone has to deal with the paperwork.

347
00:32:24.275 --> 00:32:28.858
the groceries. the money. He must be your guardian.
And he will.

348
00:32:29.399 --> 00:32:30.691
- I beg your pardon?

349
00:32:30.691 --> 00:32:34.066
- You know you need someone
to take a look at you.

350
00:32:34.108 --> 00:32:36.483
- I don't need anyone! When is
that you'll finally figure it out?

351
00:32:36.483 --> 00:32:40.316
I don't need you. her. anyone!

352
00:32:40.316 --> 00:32:42.733
- Calm down.
I don't want to hear anything.

353
00:32:42.774 --> 00:32:46.066
- I say what I want! This is my house!
- But I pay the bills.

354
00:32:46.066 --> 00:32:47.608
- With my money!

355
00:32:47.650 --> 00:32:49.774
You steal my money. then you come here and
you shit on me.

356
00:32:49.816 --> 00:32:52.483
- The money. you say? I really can trust you.
about you for the money?

357
00:32:52.525 --> 00:32:53.733
- You got me here. you understand?

358
00:32:53.733 --> 00:32:56.650
Show off your power like an unfinished dictator!

359
00:32:56.650 --> 00:32:58.608
I don't want to see you!

360
00:32:58.608 --> 00:33:00.233
- I'll come back when you've calmed down.

361
00:33:00.233 --> 00:33:02.441
- Thank God your brother doesn't have to see you.

362
00:33:03.650 --> 00:33:06.358
Do you know how you treat me? Do you?

363
00:33:06.399 --> 00:33:08.399
- Sir. don't start that again!
- Do you know?

364
00:33:08.441 --> 00:33:11.108
- He knows everything and for a long time!
- Well yes. of course!

365
00:33:11.108 --> 00:33:13.650
- I'm tired of arguing endlessly
with you on this!

366
00:33:13.691 --> 00:33:15.275
- All you do is lie to me.

367
00:33:15.275 --> 00:33:20.525
- I'm not lying! All right. that's enough! Not
I can take it anymore! We're trying to help you!

368
00:33:20.525 --> 00:33:23.566
- And I don't need your help!
I saw her in the coffin. okay?

369
00:33:23.566 --> 00:33:26.733
- I don't need your help or your money!
- Yeah. you would have left a lot sooner.

370
00:33:26.774 --> 00:33:31.774
Without me. you'd have ended up on the street!
Covered in garbage!

371
00:33:31.774 --> 00:33:33.525
- Go to hell!

372
00:33:44.816 --> 00:33:46.191
- Get the hell out of here.

373
00:33:58.566 --> 00:34:00.483
- I missed you over the weekend. Were you bored?

374
00:34:00.983 --> 00:34:02.774
- "Bored" is not the right word.

375
00:34:05.650 --> 00:34:07.774
- God! At least have mercy on my ribs!

376
00:34:25.275 --> 00:34:26.608
Did you buy the wine?

377
00:34:30.399 --> 00:34:33.358
- Wine?
- Go to Martin's.

378
00:34:36.358 --> 00:34:38.900
- I completely forgot. Was that today?

379
00:34:39.191 --> 00:34:41.566
- It doesn't matter. Go get in the shower.
I'm gonna run to the store.

380
00:34:47.066 --> 00:34:48.191
- Will Max be there?

381
00:34:48.191 --> 00:34:49.774
- I don't know. Ask him.

382
00:34:52.149 --> 00:34:54.233
What happened? Did you have a fight?

383
00:34:54.275 --> 00:34:57.441
- No. just asking.
- Okay. go take a shower.

384
00:35:08.024 --> 00:35:09.233
- Hi. how are you?

385
00:35:09.233 --> 00:35:10.983
Hey. Julien. it's me. How are you?

386
00:35:10.983 --> 00:35:13.608
- Yes. everything seems to be going well.
- Why are you speaking English?

387
00:35:14.691 --> 00:35:19.066
Aha. I'm fucking with you. This is Jules.
leave a message after the tone.

388
00:35:21.566 --> 00:35:24.066
- Hey. Julien. it's me.

389
00:35:27.774 --> 00:35:31.900
Cool. I didn't realize right away
that this was your answering machine.

390
00:35:33.024 --> 00:35:35.149
Listen. I left Mom's right now.

391
00:35:35.149 --> 00:35:39.733
I think you should know that it's six months

392
00:35:39.733 --> 00:35:42.650
which consumes nothing

393
00:35:42.650 --> 00:35:47.816
so you could say
that things are going well.

394
00:35:49.900 --> 00:35:54.399
I don't know in general whether
you have plans for the weekend

395
00:35:54.441 --> 00:35:56.233
it's Mom's birthday.

396
00:35:56.275 --> 00:35:58.275
we can arrange a dinner
or go to a restaurant.

397
00:35:59.650 --> 00:36:03.983
Sure. from New Heaven to Montreal
is a very long distance

398
00:36:04.024 --> 00:36:07.191
but I'm sure he'd be very happy
to see you.

399
00:36:08.691 --> 00:36:11.149
- Be careful with that phone. you moron!

400
00:38:19.358 --> 00:38:23.149
- I don't understand. Is he faking it?

401
00:38:24.024 --> 00:38:27.941
- I bet his English-speaking comrades
aren't half as good as him.

402
00:38:27.941 --> 00:38:30.399
- He plays in a jazz band.

403
00:38:30.399 --> 00:38:33.566
I mean he was playing. He didn't like it. did he. Marco?

404
00:38:33.608 --> 00:38:36.483
- Mom. you asked me to play
and now you won't shut up!

405
00:38:36.525 --> 00:38:39.108
- Oh. you're my God. Forgive us. Amadeus.

406
00:38:39.149 --> 00:38:42.441
We'll sit here in silence like rats.

407
00:38:46.149 --> 00:38:47.316
- Like rats!

408
00:38:56.275 --> 00:38:58.275
- What did you do in the jazz band?
- I have no idea.

409
00:38:58.566 --> 00:39:00.233
- I'm hearing everything.

410
00:39:01.774 --> 00:39:05.691
- Bye!
- Here are the stragglers!

411
00:39:05.733 --> 00:39:07.066
- Late!

412
00:39:07.108 --> 00:39:11.566
Sarah had nothing to do with it. I'm sure of it.
How are you. honey?

413
00:39:11.566 --> 00:39:15.066
- Well. for the first 20 years of my life...
you were always the one who was late.

414
00:39:15.108 --> 00:39:17.941
and now that I live alone
you always arrive on time!

415
00:39:17.941 --> 00:39:19.858
- He's right. Francine.

416
00:39:20.816 --> 00:39:24.358
- You know. Colette Kostopulos doesn't...
I expected such betrayal from you!

417
00:39:27.608 --> 00:39:28.900
- Who am I playing for?

418
00:39:32.191 --> 00:39:35.900
- Look. you're all dirty.
- This is my new look.

419
00:39:36.983 --> 00:39:38.108
- I like it.

420
00:39:44.233 --> 00:39:46.191
- There's a clock on the wall.
Why are you looking at your hand?

421
00:39:47.233 --> 00:39:49.566
- And why did you get beat on your ass with a white hood?

422
00:39:52.191 --> 00:39:54.233
- On the head. not the ass.

423
00:39:56.358 --> 00:39:57.483
- Don't move.
- It burns!

424
00:39:57.483 --> 00:39:58.483
- That's normal.

425
00:40:00.650 --> 00:40:03.024
- What will you do in Australia if you find yourself
with a bloody forehead?

426
00:40:04.024 --> 00:40:05.233
- All right. that's enough.

427
00:40:06.941 --> 00:40:07.983
- They didn't do anything to me.

428
00:40:09.399 --> 00:40:12.108
It's not slow. I fell.

429
00:40:13.441 --> 00:40:15.483
I tripped on the street.

430
00:40:19.941 --> 00:40:21.024
- What are you gonna do there?

431
00:40:24.316 --> 00:40:28.358
- You mean in general
or day to day?

432
00:40:28.858 --> 00:40:29.900
- Both of them.

433
00:40:35.316 --> 00:40:37.941
- I'll look for a job. what else.

434
00:40:39.774 --> 00:40:41.108
- You already have a job here.

435
00:40:42.316 --> 00:40:44.816
Do you feel bad at the bar with me?

436
00:40:48.399 --> 00:40:51.316
And with this jacket covered in blood.
Drop it. at least.

437
00:40:51.358 --> 00:40:53.358
Get something out of Eric's clothes.

438
00:40:58.733 --> 00:41:03.066
- Tell me. do you have plans
for Friday night?

439
00:41:04.650 --> 00:41:08.233
- I don't know. I'll work for Caro.
she's leaving at midnight.

440
00:41:11.108 --> 00:41:14.691
- It's just that Sharif my friend
from a party.

441
00:41:14.733 --> 00:41:16.316
We're all going.

442
00:41:18.399 --> 00:41:20.149
- Is that an invitation or a date?

443
00:41:21.691 --> 00:41:25.275
- No. I'm looking for someone to give me
a ride. Yes: a date.

444
00:41:30.275 --> 00:41:35.149
- You're asking me to spend an evening
in the company of drunks who make a mess

445
00:41:35.149 --> 00:41:36.941
for stupid puns?

446
00:41:38.066 --> 00:41:42.691
- Well. generally. yes. Is that interesting to you?

447
00:41:43.108 --> 00:41:47.441
- Not really? All right. I'm coming.

448
00:41:54.191 --> 00:41:56.525
- This is stupid!
- How was I supposed to know?

449
00:41:56.566 --> 00:41:59.858
Jean-Marc said to me. "I have a new boss.
She's from Jamaica.

450
00:41:59.858 --> 00:42:03.275
we call her 'Ilsa the wolf' and she's always
dressed like a nun"

451
00:42:03.275 --> 00:42:06.275
I'll alert the guests and Jocelyn.

452
00:42:06.316 --> 00:42:09.525
coming with a new girl.
A tall. refined girl.

453
00:42:09.566 --> 00:42:10.774
- Legs coming out of the ears.

454
00:42:10.816 --> 00:42:12.858
I start talking:

455
00:42:12.900 --> 00:42:15.566
"Jean-Marc's boss lady dresses
like a nun

456
00:42:15.608 --> 00:42:18.149
wants to appear holier than the pope."

457
00:42:18.191 --> 00:42:20.233
- And that was her!
- That was her!

458
00:42:21.275 --> 00:42:23.983
- They have to save us!
Lock it somewhere and throw away the key!

459
00:42:23.983 --> 00:42:24.983
- I'm telling you!

460
00:42:25.024 --> 00:42:26.774
Turns out it wasn't
Jocelyn's new girlfriend

461
00:42:26.816 --> 00:42:28.608
It was her. Ilsa the wolf!

462
00:42:28.608 --> 00:42:29.691
- Nightmare.

463
00:42:29.733 --> 00:42:32.358
- They came together.
she sat down and listened to everything!

464
00:42:36.024 --> 00:42:39.941
From Jamaica - what the hell?
I've gotten redder than she has.

465
00:42:39.983 --> 00:42:41.483
She was white as milk!

466
00:42:41.525 --> 00:42:44.774
- It's true!
- Tell him! You saw it!

467
00:42:50.650 --> 00:42:53.441
- Erica was given such a task.
