01:02:58.191 --> 01:03:00.983
- I rarely come here. but the fillies that you have here
are a sight for sore eyes.

706
01:03:00.983 --> 01:03:03.358
Every time McGill sends an intern.

707
01:03:03.358 --> 01:03:07.233
They're lustful. energetic.
confident brunettes.

708
01:03:07.233 --> 01:03:09.983
Well. just turn off the lights!

709
01:03:17.941 --> 01:03:20.608
Matt. am I boring you? Tell me honestly.

710
01:03:20.608 --> 01:03:25.483
- No no. it's not you. It's me.

711
01:03:26.691 --> 01:03:29.483
- We can speak French.
if it's easier for you.

712
01:03:29.900 --> 01:03:32.774
- I'm a little worried because I'm
late for something.

713
01:03:33.691 --> 01:03:36.816
- Are you late? Where to?
- To say hello to a friend of mine.

714
01:03:37.608 --> 01:03:41.316
- Is he leaving?
- Yes. for two years.

715
01:03:42.024 --> 01:03:43.316
- Are you close as friends?

716
01:03:46.108 --> 01:03:47.650
Very. very close?

717
01:03:49.525 --> 01:03:52.066
- No. I wouldn't say that.

718
01:03:54.525 --> 01:03:58.774
Only my mother arranges this
party

719
01:03:59.108 --> 01:04:00.774
you know how it is...

720
01:04:02.399 --> 01:04:04.275
- Annoying?
- Annoying.

721
01:04:04.275 --> 01:04:07.149
- My poor boy. Yes. I'm joking.

722
01:04:11.441 --> 01:04:12.733
May I?

723
01:04:14.608 --> 01:04:15.816
- I'll pay for it.

724
01:04:19.358 --> 01:04:20.399
- All right. he's paying.

725
01:04:35.399 --> 01:04:40.441
So. in the garage there are vegetables - in the fridge there is cheese. crab sauce there is.

726
01:04:40.441 --> 01:04:41.983
It's all there.

727
01:04:43.983 --> 01:04:46.441
Next time write it more
baby. Francine Lamy!

728
01:04:59.316 --> 01:05:01.608
I made you meat pies.
Max!

729
01:05:01.650 --> 01:05:04.399
- I know. Francine. Thank you!
That wasn't necessary.

730
01:05:04.399 --> 01:05:07.108
- Stop talking nonsense. please.
- No. I mean it.

731
01:05:07.149 --> 01:05:09.733
- To think you'll find these things in Sydney (?)

732
01:05:09.733 --> 01:05:12.566
In Oceania the meat pies
they don't grow on trees!

733
01:05:12.608 --> 01:05:16.691
- In Oceania? Even better in southern Indochina. Francine!

734
01:05:16.733 --> 01:05:19.441
- Well. sure. Ladies and gentlemen.
Rivets is getting smart!

735
01:05:19.483 --> 01:05:23.816
- If you want I can run to the store and
bring you a couple of bottles of bourbon!

736
01:05:23.816 --> 01:05:27.983
- Calm down a little bit. princess.
- How interesting you are.

737
01:05:28.024 --> 01:05:29.900
- Come here princess. and help me!

738
01:05:29.900 --> 01:05:33.191
When you stop talking nonsense.
life will have gone on!

739
01:05:33.691 --> 01:05:34.858
Come on. come on. let's go!

740
01:05:35.441 --> 01:05:36.900
- I'll be there in two minutes.

741
01:05:43.900 --> 01:05:45.650
- Sir. how long I've been held up.

742
01:05:45.650 --> 01:05:47.900
You've been late for an hour and you're whining at the door.
what did you bring?

743
01:05:47.900 --> 01:05:51.858
Your father could invent
better excuses.

744
01:05:51.900 --> 01:05:54.024
-I've been texting you.
Is this the end of matriarchy?

745
01:05:54.066 --> 01:05:58.358
The matriarch is in the kitchen today.
I don't have time for texting!

746
01:05:58.358 --> 01:06:01.066
- Why are you buying a cell phone
you forget around the room?

747
01:06:01.108 --> 01:06:03.483
- A representative of the generation of
Internet. everybody be quiet!

748
01:06:03.483 --> 01:06:06.733
- Oh. you're here!
- Yeah. I didn't wait.

749
01:06:06.733 --> 01:06:07.900
- Is everything all right?

750
01:06:07.900 --> 01:06:10.858
- I got held up by this guy in Toronto.
I couldn't go anywhere.

751
01:06:10.858 --> 01:06:13.858
- "I couldn't go anywhere." it's the same one.
what to say "I'm not to blame"

752
01:06:13.900 --> 01:06:15.983
where there's one. there's the other.
A family history.

753
01:06:16.024 --> 01:06:17.149
- Mom. come on.

754
01:06:17.149 --> 01:06:19.900
- Max has been biting his nails for an hour.

755
01:06:19.900 --> 01:06:23.191
- That's his problem. He can talk. he's got a tongue.

756
01:06:23.191 --> 01:06:24.900
- He's not comfortable here without you!

757
01:06:24.900 --> 01:06:27.691
- Did you bring him the letter of recommendation?
Your father's.

758
01:06:27.691 --> 01:06:28.983
- What letter?
- All right. that's enough!

759
01:06:29.483 --> 01:06:32.399
- He needs to get a job at
Sydney. the bosses are asking for recommendations.

760
01:06:32.441 --> 01:06:35.275
- I know. but it's not my fault.

761
01:06:35.316 --> 01:06:37.358
- Ah! "It's not my fault."
- "Ah!"

762
01:06:37.399 --> 01:06:40.608
- On the third attempt I go personally
to this collection centre

763
01:06:41.275 --> 01:06:43.774
and at noon the package is ready
to be sent. I saw it!

764
01:06:43.774 --> 01:06:48.691
- Please. in the kitchen. we must keep this secret.
Thank you.

765
01:06:48.733 --> 01:06:50.774
- Yes yes. it's a secret for everyone.

766
01:06:50.774 --> 01:06:53.691
We need to talk about a book
which is called "The Secret."

767
01:06:53.733 --> 01:06:55.108
- I wonder if there's any switch

768
01:06:55.149 --> 01:06:56.608
which may disable
your chatter.

769
01:06:57.733 --> 01:06:59.691
- All right. then.
- What should we do?

770
01:06:59.900 --> 01:07:02.441
- Come here. Matthias!
- Aha! Whisper!

771
01:07:02.441 --> 01:07:07.191
- So. you talk first. make a little speech.

772
01:07:08.566 --> 01:07:09.900
Matt. Matt.

773
01:07:09.900 --> 01:07:11.525
- Okay. I'll make this speech. Then what?

774
01:07:11.566 --> 01:07:14.900
- A little speech. then the
let's get a sweater.

775
01:07:14.900 --> 01:07:18.316
- First the sweater. because the iPad cost
more. Well. you got it.

776
01:07:19.399 --> 01:07:22.358
- And after the presents there will be a cake
with berries!

777
01:07:22.399 --> 01:07:23.441
- What other fruits are there?

778
01:07:23.483 --> 01:07:25.441
- Strawberries. raspberries. blackberries.

779
01:07:25.483 --> 01:07:27.774
- What's not clear to you about the words "berries"?
All right. let's go!

780
01:07:33.024 --> 01:07:34.983
- They crashed.
- Come on.

781
01:07:34.983 --> 01:07:36.650
- I'm telling you. crash.

782
01:07:36.650 --> 01:07:39.024
- Attention. please!

783
01:07:39.566 --> 01:07:41.024
Shut up. guys!

784
01:07:41.024 --> 01:07:44.483
You. of course. are no longer a child but you are still
my favorite guy.

785
01:07:44.733 --> 01:07:45.858
And you too. my dear Sarah.

786
01:07:48.858 --> 01:07:52.024
Dear Maxime. I know I don't
you like long speeches.

787
01:07:52.024 --> 01:07:53.066
- And yet...

788
01:07:53.108 --> 01:07:57.608
- But you don't have a choice.
You go and leave us

789
01:07:58.691 --> 01:07:59.900
for two years.

790
01:08:00.983 --> 01:08:04.566
So Matt wants to tell you something
to say goodbye

791
01:08:06.275 --> 01:08:09.483
- Max. Max.

792
01:08:11.733 --> 01:08:13.441
I wouldn't want to.

793
01:08:14.733 --> 01:08:17.566
I know you don't like it...

794
01:08:19.399 --> 01:08:23.608
have every look
so I'll try to keep it short.

795
01:08:36.441 --> 01:08:39.441
I'm sorry. I probably should have sketched
something in advance.

796
01:08:39.483 --> 01:08:41.066
- Come on. come on!

797
01:08:44.066 --> 01:08:46.441
- It will be very strange and unusual to be
here without you.

798
01:08:47.858 --> 01:08:49.691
but at the same time...

799
01:08:54.566 --> 01:08:56.358
Oh. my goodness. how can I say this.

800
01:08:59.774 --> 01:09:01.399
We're gonna miss you so much. but I know...

801
01:09:01.941 --> 01:09:05.441
that you'll come back to us
like a different person.

802
01:09:06.650 --> 01:09:09.566
With a new strength. a new energy.

803
01:09:10.191 --> 01:09:12.608
And I'm sure.

804
01:09:14.941 --> 01:09:19.608
I'm sure there. in those faraway lands.
a lot of interesting discoveries await you.

805
01:09:20.566 --> 01:09:25.566
That will enrich your world. So there!

806
01:09:27.733 --> 01:09:31.399
Of course we'll miss you.

807
01:09:31.399 --> 01:09:34.983
I think I have the right to speak
on behalf of everyone. For Max!

808
01:09:36.650 --> 01:09:38.525
- I thought you were more eloquent.

809
01:09:38.566 --> 01:09:41.941
- Well. then. for Max!
- For Max!

810
01:09:41.941 --> 01:09:42.941
- Max!
- Max!

811
01:09:42.983 --> 01:09:44.191
- Cheers. Max.
- For Max!

812
01:09:48.233 --> 01:09:50.900
- And now presents. presents. presents!

813
01:09:57.483 --> 01:10:00.399
- How many times do I have to say it.
I hate presents!

814
01:10:04.358 --> 01:10:08.149
- Delicious. as always!

815
01:10:08.525 --> 01:10:09.941
Especially the meat pies.

816
01:10:11.358 --> 01:10:14.941
- See you again
before you leave on Wednesday?

817
01:10:14.941 --> 01:10:17.441
- Yeah. I'm leaving Friday.
- Really?

818
01:10:17.441 --> 01:10:19.024
- Yes. Friday.
I'll come back for a suitcase.

819
01:10:19.066 --> 01:10:21.733
And why did you decide that on Wednesday?

820
01:10:22.483 --> 01:10:25.525
Nonsense. You shouldn't spend money.
- Come on. stop it.

821
01:10:25.566 --> 01:10:28.941
- Don't be silly!
And anyway. this is from all of us.

822
01:10:30.608 --> 01:10:33.650
- Max. can I send
the GPS coordinates to Sharif?

823
01:10:34.024 --> 01:10:36.441
- I left my phone in the car.

824
01:10:36.483 --> 01:10:40.149
- What are you talking about? Did I hear right?
Benjamin Sharif?

825
01:10:40.149 --> 01:10:43.441
- No. Omar Sharif. the actor who died.
We're on our way to see him.

826
01:10:43.483 --> 01:10:44.858
- Yes. Francine. your beautiful Sharif.
favorite.

827
01:10:44.858 --> 01:10:48.566
- If I could then I'd go with you.

828
01:10:48.566 --> 01:10:50.733
- What? Give it a chance.

829
01:10:50.733 --> 01:10:52.774
- Is he still studying. our Benjamin?

830
01:10:52.816 --> 01:10:54.774
When will you become a teacher?

831
01:10:54.774 --> 01:10:56.149
- He's already giving lessons.

832
01:10:56.149 --> 01:11:00.316
- Stop it. I wasn't born yesterday. What was your diploma?

833
01:11:00.358 --> 01:11:01.399
- Here. call him and ask him.

834
01:11:01.441 --> 01:11:05.149
- Don't tempt me. However. it's much more
nice by Alain Delon

835
01:11:05.191 --> 01:11:08.275
and Peter Sellers
With that Moroccan charm.

836
01:11:08.275 --> 01:11:10.691
I've always been fascinated. (?)

837
01:11:10.733 --> 01:11:12.983
Like Matt's dad. for example.
wonderful Portuguese.

838
01:11:13.024 --> 01:11:15.358
wine connoisseur and great conversationalist. but it wasn't enough.

839
01:11:15.358 --> 01:11:17.358
- Guys. I have to say goodbye.

840
01:11:17.358 --> 01:11:21.024
- What? You're not going to Sharif's?
- Poor Benjamin boy!

841
01:11:21.275 --> 01:11:25.275
- Seriously. I'm too tired today.
- I thought you were going.

842
01:11:26.233 --> 01:11:27.900
- Okay. but you know what I think.

843
01:11:27.900 --> 01:11:31.233
- And I've already told Felish Mokett that you're going to play
in his student project.

844
01:11:31.275 --> 01:11:34.108
- Screw you.
- You've got to be kidding me. Relax. Matt.

845
01:11:34.108 --> 01:11:36.233
- I don't understand.
why don't you go?

846
01:11:36.233 --> 01:11:37.983
- The week has been difficult.

847
01:11:38.024 --> 01:11:39.191
- Matt. can I talk to you for a second?

848
01:11:40.566 --> 01:11:43.650
- Max. I'll see you another time?
- Oh. sure.

849
01:11:43.650 --> 01:11:45.399
- We'll be in touch.
- Matt!

850
01:11:51.525 --> 01:11:54.608
- Look. I can take you there
and take a cab back.

851
01:11:54.650 --> 01:11:57.650
- Sarah. it's not that. It's just that
I don't want to go. I'm tired.

852
01:11:58.399 --> 01:12:00.900
- Matt. shut up please. two minutes.
Listen to me.

853
01:12:01.233 --> 01:12:03.566
- It's only 7:30.
You're not a hundred years old.

854
01:12:03.900 --> 01:12:07.191
You took your partner to lunch.
you didn't translate "War and Peace"!

855
01:12:09.358 --> 01:12:12.525
- All right. I'll go...

856
01:12:14.191 --> 01:12:15.399
- I'll wait for you in the car.

857
01:12:47.733 --> 01:12:50.066
- I don't have to go to Bordeaux. Bring me
in Longueuil. stupid!

858
01:12:50.066 --> 01:12:51.566
- What are you doing. huh?

859
01:12:52.149 --> 01:12:57.149
- I'm taking these stupid clothes off!
I hate them.

860
01:12:57.149 --> 01:12:58.858
I only put them on to please
to Francine.

861
01:12:58.858 --> 01:13:01.233
- Tell that to the guy with the funny guys...
on T-shirts.

862
01:13:01.275 --> 01:13:05.191
- Leave me alone. I. at least. don't dress
like a faggot.

863
01:13:05.983 --> 01:13:07.691
- Who's the faggot?

864
01:13:07.691 --> 01:13:09.858
- Frank. send her back.
- Who. me?

865
01:13:09.858 --> 01:13:13.733
- Well. yeah. you Frank. Back off. I said.

866
01:13:14.149 --> 01:13:16.275
No. you're running it.

867
01:13:18.608 --> 01:13:21.191
- Damn. it's so hard to film
a station?

868
01:13:21.191 --> 01:13:23.108
- Get off me. Brass!
- Your hands are crooked!

869
01:13:23.149 --> 01:13:25.816
- Ah. this is the same song. I'm sorry.

870
01:13:25.858 --> 01:13:29.816
- This one's from when we got high on mushrooms and we got
sitting around watching "The Barbarian Invasions"?

871
01:13:29.858 --> 01:13:31.233
- That's right! And then we went

872
01:13:31.275 --> 01:13:33.399
out of town until morning. talking about vulgarity.

873
01:13:33.399 --> 01:13:37.441
- And then we had a contest to see who would have
invented a 12-letter adjective!

874
01:13:37.483 --> 01:13:39.650
- I'm trying. don't pull me!
- Damn. we're gonna miss him now!

875
01:14:35.275 --> 01:14:37.774
- At some point. I realized
that I'm past the jokes and the songs.

876
01:14:38.525 --> 01:14:40.441
I'm going to see him today.

877
01:14:41.233 --> 01:14:43.275
but in general. I want to pass
more time with you.

878
01:14:43.316 --> 01:14:45.525
We have to somehow get the
distance from this company.

879
01:14:46.858 --> 01:14:49.941
- I don't mean all of them. of course.
But one or two.

880
01:14:51.441 --> 01:14:53.233
- You plan things ahead of time?

881
01:14:54.608 --> 01:14:56.900
These things usually happen by themselves.

882
01:14:59.900 --> 01:15:01.108
- Yes. but...

883
01:15:01.149 --> 01:15:03.399
- I understand you had some business

884
01:15:03.733 --> 01:15:06.024
but only half an hour with friends
is such an unbearable burden for you?

885
01:15:06.566 --> 01:15:08.900
And I know that your mom sometimes
is not easy to sustain

886
01:15:08.941 --> 01:15:10.650
I know. but you have to have
more tact. Matt.

887
01:15:11.024 --> 01:15:13.525
Otherwise. I don't know who could be next.

888
01:15:13.566 --> 01:15:14.566
- Yes. but...

889
01:15:14.566 --> 01:15:15.733
- Let me finish. Matt!

890
01:15:17.191 --> 01:15:19.441
This speech you gave
for Max today

891
01:15:20.275 --> 01:15:22.233
You think I made someone happy?

892
01:15:25.191 --> 01:15:28.233
And it didn't occur to you
that Matt might take offense to.

893
01:15:28.275 --> 01:15:29.733
if you don't go with them?

894
01:15:32.233 --> 01:15:34.525
And I don't... You're leaving now?

895
01:15:34.983 --> 01:15:35.983
- Yes. but...

896
01:15:35.983 --> 01:15:37.691
- Why do you always have to think only of yourself?

897
01:15:37.691 --> 01:15:40.275
- And what. I'm supposed to think about Max all the time?

898
01:15:40.275 --> 01:15:41.650
Why are you telling me
this. now?

899
01:15:41.816 --> 01:15:43.566
What. am I under investigation?

900
01:15:49.691 --> 01:15:50.941
This is all because of the movie. right?

901
01:15:53.358 --> 01:15:55.066
I knew it. that's why
damn movie.

902
01:15:56.149 --> 01:15:57.483
Am I right?

903
01:15:58.024 --> 01:16:01.108
Sarah! Sarah!

904
01:16:01.108 --> 01:16:03.483
- Matt. I don't understand what
you're saying!

905
01:16:03.525 --> 01:16:05.816
- Stop pretending. Have you seen this
Erika's crappy movie!

906
01:16:06.441 --> 01:16:08.525
Sarah. he means nothing to me!

907
01:16:08.525 --> 01:16:09.733
We had a discussion.

908
01:16:09.774 --> 01:16:12.566
I didn't even want to do it! Do you understand?

909
01:16:16.316 --> 01:16:19.733
So let's forget about it
of everything else.

910
01:16:23.441 --> 01:16:25.650
- Now we turn right?
- Yes.

911
01:16:54.024 --> 01:16:55.441
Have fun.

912
01:17:20.900 --> 01:17:22.483
- Yeah. let's go.

913
01:17:28.024 --> 01:17:30.191
All right then. everybody be quiet.
while I explain the rules.

914
01:17:30.608 --> 01:17:34.024
- Guys!
- Sharif. I know it's your house. but be quiet.

915
01:17:34.358 --> 01:17:35.900
- A toast to ten years of friendship.

916
01:17:35.941 --> 01:17:37.316
- It doesn't matter. So. first shift.

917
01:17:37.358 --> 01:17:40.358
Say what you want but avoid
derivative words.

918
01:17:40.358 --> 01:17:41.441
- What words do you derive from that?

919
01:17:41.483 --> 01:17:45.191
- Well. for example. "housewife - housewife".
"lover-lover" and so on.

920
01:17:46.275 --> 01:17:47.858
Round two: Just one word.

921
01:17:48.108 --> 01:17:50.774
- Brass. now you got one in the forehead.
- Why are you bothering me?

922
01:17:50.774 --> 01:17:54.149
- Round three: pantomime. It doesn't matter
there must not be a single sound. Do you understand. Brass?

923
01:17:54.399 --> 01:17:57.275
Pantomime! How long do we do
30 or 45 seconds?

924
01:17:57.275 --> 01:17:58.774
- Make it 30.
- 45!

925
01:17:59.024 --> 01:18:00.858
- All right. 45! Unbreakable.

926
01:18:00.900 --> 01:18:04.483
Then let's get started. ladies and gentlemen!

927
01:20:02.316 --> 01:20:03.483
- Runner.

928
01:20:07.108 --> 01:20:09.774
- I know. Usain Bolt!

929
01:20:10.399 --> 01:20:12.108
- God. Matt. I'm scared of you.

930
01:20:12.149 --> 01:20:15.275
- Shut up! It's my turn now!

931
01:20:18.108 --> 01:20:21.691
- Rivett. Rivette. mix them up!
- It's his fault!

932
01:20:32.691 --> 01:20:35.108
- And I didn't hear it.
- I don't understand why you're getting so upset.

933
01:20:36.316 --> 01:20:38.983
- You didn't guess.
- Owens? Jesse Owens!

934
01:20:45.233 --> 01:20:47.358
